<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is good, for journalists, to ask Sam Bankma=
n-Fried where all the money went, but he is not going to tell you. The poss=
ibilities are:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">He knows where the money went, and he=
 has huge incentives to lie about it, or</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">He doesn=E2=80=99t know where the money went, as he sort of keeps sa=
ying, and he will just pass along his confusion to you.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is not some third possibility where you =
can sit Bankman-Fried down and he will be like =E2=80=9Chere is a detailed =
timeline of all the innocent mistakes we made and how much customer money=
=C2=A0each one vaporized.=E2=80=9D If he had those details available to him=
, he would not have vaporized the money. Or he would have, but the mistakes=
 were not innocent, and he will not describe them accurately. Either way,=
=C2=A0you will not get a satisfying explanation, from him.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The person who will tell you=C2=A0where the mo=
ney went at Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s crypto exchange, FTX, and its affiliate=
d trading firm, Alameda Research, is John Ray, six months from now. Ray is =
the current chief executive officer of FTX, appointed moments before it fil=
ed for bankruptcy, and the former bankruptcy wrangler of disasters like Enr=
on. He <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29860385.27=
3543/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMT=
cvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1mdHgtd2FzLW5vdC12ZXJ5LWNhcmVmdWw_Y21wa=
WQ9QkJEMTIwMTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3Ns=
ZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMjAxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB63c78ee3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">  harrumphed into bankruptcy court</a> last m=
onth to be like =E2=80=9Cthis is the biggest mess I=E2=80=99ve ever seen, a=
nd I=E2=80=99ve seen Enron,=E2=80=9D and if I were him I=E2=80=99d say that=
 <em>constantly=C2=A0</em>to my kids. Ray=E2=80=99s=C2=A0well-paid and fran=
kly very interesting=C2=A0job is to sort it out, and I assume eventually he=
 will. That sorting apparently involves, like, Googling news articles to se=
e what venture capital investments FTX made, because FTX did not itself kee=
p a list of its own investments. That is what we are dealing with here.=C2=
=A0=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But Ray is=C2=A0methodically piecing together =
the accounts, not giving interviews, and keeping his complaints to court fi=
lings. Meanwhile Bankman-Fried is at loose ends in his Bahamas penthouse an=
d seems to be spending his time calling up journalists and compulsively con=
fessing to =E2=80=A6=C2=A0whatever it is he thinks he is confessing to? =E2=
=80=9CI didn=E2=80=99t ever try to commit fraud on anyone,=E2=80=9D he <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29860385.273543/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMzAvYmFua21hbi1mc=
mllZC1kZW5pZXMtdHJ5aW5nLXRvLWNvbW1pdC1mcmF1ZC1hdC1mYWxsZW4tZnR4LWVtcGlyZT9j=
bXBpZD1CQkQxMjAxMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV=
3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjEyMDEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cBc24b468a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">  told Andrew Ross Sorkin yesterday</a>, b=
ut, otherwise.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here are the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/29860385.273543/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F=
0Y2g_dj1JeW9HZHdWSXdXdw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3ea58e44" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> video</=
a> and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29860385.27=
3543/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8xMi8wMS9idXNpbmVzcy9kZWFsYm9vay=
9zYW0tYmFua21hbi1mcmllZC1kZWFsYm9vay1pbnRlcnZpZXctdHJhbnNjcmlwdC5odG1sP2Nhb=
XBhaWduX2lkPTQmZW1jPWVkaXRfZGtfMjAyMjEyMDEmaW5zdGFuY2VfaWQ9Nzg5ODEmbmw9ZGVh=
bGJvb2smcmVnaV9pZD0xMjUzMjc3NSZzZWdtZW50X2lkPTExNDY3NCZ0ZT0xJnVzZXJfaWQ9M2M=
1YzI1Nzk5NDBiNDJhY2JkOTVkOWJhMjA2MzFkODM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfd41b43e"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;"> transcript</a> of Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s interview with Sorkin a=
t the DealBook conference yesterday. Here is an <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29860385.273543/aHR0cHM6Ly9ueW1hZy5jb20vaW50Z=
WxsaWdlbmNlci9hcnRpY2xlL3NhbS1iYW5rbWFuLWZyaWVkLWZ0eC1pbnRlcnZpZXcuaHRtbA/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB85c6e601" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> interview with Jen Wieczner</a> =
in New York magazine, which was published today though conducted on Nov. 17=
. Here is an interview with <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/29860385.273543/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZG1vcm5pbmdhbWVyaWNhLmNvbS9Cd=
XNpbmVzcy9zdG9yeS9mdHhzLXNhbS1iYW5rbWFuLWZyaWVkLWRlbmllcy1pbXByb3Blci1jdXN0=
b21lci1mdW5kcy05NDIzMzEyNQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa32d4d2c" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Geor=
ge Stephanopoulos on =E2=80=9CGood Morning America=E2=80=9D</a>.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I want to give a stylized version of Bankman-F=
ried=E2=80=99s account of what went wrong at FTX and Alameda. It goes somet=
hing like this:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">FTX International was a crypto exchan=
ge for sophisticated margin traders.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#fo=
otnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border=
-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none=
 !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-bloc=
k;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0A =E2=80=9Ccrypto exchange=E2=80=9D is both an exchange =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0a place where people can meet to buy and sell crypto =E2=80=94=C2=A0b=
ut also a broker-dealer, a firm that holds its customers=E2=80=99 crypto fo=
r them and gives them financing.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">E=
veryone trading on FTX was basically borrowing money from FTX to put on lev=
eraged crypto trades, or lending out the crypto in their FTX accounts to ea=
rn interest, or both. This=C2=A0<em>necessarily=C2=A0</em>means that the cu=
stomers=E2=80=99 crypto was not segregated: If you=E2=80=99re lending out y=
our crypto to earn interest, or borrowing crypto to make bigger trades, you=
 can=E2=80=99t expect your crypto to all sit in a segregated account doing =
nothing. If you are trading via leveraged perpetual futures, a big FTX prod=
uct, you certainly can=E2=80=99t expect your crypto to all be sitting there=
 waiting for you: You don=E2=80=99t <em>own=C2=A0</em>any crypto; you just =
have a derivative trade with FTX.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=
One very important trader on FTX was Alameda Research, which had huge lever=
aged positions on FTX.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Alameda=E2=
=80=99s position was overcollateralized, but FTX had a little bit of an $8 =
billion accounting boo-boo, so it thought Alameda=E2=80=99s position was le=
ss leveraged than it actually was.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;"=
>Then there was a huge sudden correlated drop in the prices of crypto asset=
s, which left Alameda undercollateralized, and FTX =E2=80=94=C2=A0due to th=
e accounting boo-boo =E2=80=94 was surprised to find out how undercollatera=
lized it was.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Other traders notice=
d this and withdrew money from FTX, creating a =E2=80=9Crun on the bank.=E2=
=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The run on the bank also le=
