olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;">  mentions</a> =E2=80=9Cthe secret exemption of Alameda from certai=
n aspects of FTX.com=E2=80=99s auto-liquidation protocol.=E2=80=9D The main=
 selling point of FTX was not true when it mattered.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That seems bad? Yes, of course, it is bad for =
the reasons that Bankman-Fried now says, that he should have monitored Alam=
eda=E2=80=99s positions and taken down their risk. (And that FTX=E2=80=99s =
calculation of Alameda=E2=80=99s position should have been, you know, corre=
ct.) But it is also bad because FTX was going around=C2=A0<em>misrepresenti=
ng=C2=A0</em>how it managed risk.=C2=A0That stuff about a computer that saw=
 everyone=E2=80=99s positions, knew the value of their collateral,=C2=A0and=
 acted instantly to close any positions without a loss to FTX all seems to =
have been misleading. In fact, FTX apparently=C2=A0managed its most importa=
nt market risk =E2=80=94=C2=A0Alameda=E2=80=99s huge leveraged position =E2=
=80=94 more or less=C2=A0by someone writing Alameda=E2=80=99s position on a=
 napkin, and getting the math=C2=A0wrong, and then handing the napkin to Ba=
nkman-Fried, and Bankman-Fried being=C2=A0<em>afraid to look at the napkin<=
/em>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A minimal but still pretty bad form of fraud a=
t FTX would be:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">In fact FTX lost its customers=E2=80=
=99 money through well-intentioned but incompetent bumbling; it just didn=
=E2=80=99t keep very good track of customer money or risk or anything else.=
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It lied,=C2=A0constantly, about h=
ow carefully it was keeping track of risk and customer money.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The story of FTX that we have heard over the l=
ast month =E2=80=94=C2=A0from Bankman-Fried, from Ray, from everyone else =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0is that it was a bunch of disorganized children who had no i=
dea what they were doing or where the money was. The story of FTX that we h=
eard =E2=80=94=C2=A0from Bankman-Fried and everyone else =E2=80=94=C2=A0<em=
>before=C2=A0</em>this month was that FTX=C2=A0<em>were the adults in the r=
oom</em>, the hyper-competent, risk-focused, regulation-friendly, sophistic=
ated crypto exchange. If you go around telling that story it really has to =
be true, or true-ish, or arguably true! If now you go around being like =E2=
=80=9Cah, accounting, risk management, we never really understood=C2=A0thos=
e things,=E2=80=9D that is not a good defense!</p>
